Package org.opengis.util

Interface LocalName

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Comparable<GenericName>, GenericName
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    MemberName, TypeName
    @UML(identifier="LocalName",
     specification=ISO_19103)
public interface LocalName
extends GenericName
    Identifier within a name space for a local object. Local names are names which are directly accessible to and maintained by a NameSpace. Names are local to one and only one name space. The name space within which they are local is indicated by the scope.
    Since:
    2.0
    See Also:
    NameFactory.createLocalName(NameSpace, CharSequence)

    • Method Summary

      Modifier and Type Method Description
      int depth()
      Returns always 1 for a local name.
      List<? extends LocalName> getParsedNames()
      Returns a singleton containing only this, since this name is itself a local name.
      LocalName head()
      Returns this since this object is already a local name.
      LocalName tip()
      Returns this since this object is already a local name.
      String toString()
      Returns a locale-independent string representation of this local name.
